dReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3708.topic&index=110>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: Kerryn</span><hr size=1> I'mnot sure that I grasp the sentiment amongst players here regarding monk tanking abilities.  There are three pure melee classes:  Warriors, Monks, and Rogues.  Paladins, Rangers, and Shadowknights are hybrids and have swirly little spell effects that add a LOT of power to their class.  Rogues are quite simply the highest melee damage in the game, bar none.  They also wear chain class armors.  Warriors are plate class and have the all-important Taunt button.  They have piles of hp and gear focussed towards AC.<br>
<br>
Monks therefore SHOULD be able to tank second to warriors, IMNSO.  They shouldn't be AS effective or MORE effective, but they aren't anywhere close as it stands.  Without uber armor, a monk sits just above 2khp, which means that two blows from your average uber mob is instant death.  Ok, with full raid buffs, you might double that to 4k.  The problem here is that the uber nodrop armors add WAY too much in comparison to existing monk specific equipment.  So the solution is to nerf ALL monks?  That sounds silly to me.  I certainly don't relish pulling for a group if I take more damage than before.  FD, for those non monks out there, doesn't actually work properly and never has.  Monks die pulling all the time as it is.  If you increase melee damage to go with those lovely new resists, pulling may well become a lost art.<br>
<br>
I keep seeing people saying that monks can't have both high offensive and high defensive skills at the same time.  We don't.  Our offensive damage is second best, but we have virtually no AA skills or discs that enhance offense and the majority of monks are still using Kunark-era weaponry.  We have a pretty good number of defensive and damage avoidance skills, but many depend on being the one getting attacked (you know, the TANK), so these would be useless if we couldn't get hit without keeling over.  I'm not seeing any monks replacing warriors in groups or major encounters, so I'm kind of wondering why this nerf bat is aimed in the monkly direction.  If the high end game is broken, how about fixing the high end game and leaving the lower monks who will never even fight the AoW, muchless stand toe-to-toe with him, well enough alone? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udraconbattlehammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dracon Battlehammer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 393<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/10/02 6:31:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3708.topic&index=112>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kiliara</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I'mnot sure that I grasp the sentiment amongst players here regarding monk tanking abilities. There are three pure melee classes: Warriors, Monks, and Rogues. Paladins, Rangers, and Shadowknights are hybrids and have swirly little spell effects that add a LOT of power to their class. Rogues are quite simply the highest melee damage in the game, bar none. They also wear chain class armors. Warriors are plate class and have the all-im